item.description:
Say you want to check if a specific element exists in an array. There&rsquo;s a couple of ways to do that:
ES5 indexOf() indexOf returns the index of the first matching item found, or -1 if not found.
// check if a Fortnite ninja exists in the array const ninjas = [&#39;Alchemist&#39;, &#39;Brawler&#39;, &#39;Skirmisher&#39;, &#39;Harvester&#39;] console.log(ninjas.indexOf(&#39;Brawler&#39;)) // 1 console.log(ninjas.indexOf(&#39;Harvester&#39;)) // 3 console.log(ninjas.indexOf(&#39;Assassin&#39;)) // -1 (doesn&#39;t exist)  lastIndexOf() lastIndexOf() returns the index of the last matching item found, or -1 if not found.
